BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:zmina-resilience-showcasing-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260914
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260915
SUMMARY:Deadline: ZMINA Resilience: Support for International Showcasing of
  Co-Creation Projects
DESCRIPTION:Second strand of the ZMINA: Resilience project (run by IZOLYATS
 IA Foundation (UA) and Malý Berlín (SK) with Trans Europe Halles (SE))\,
  funding the international showcasing and public presentation of artistic 
 works CO-CREATED by Ukrainian and other Creative Europe cultural organisat
 ions. Where the co-creation strand funds making the work\, this strand fun
 ds bringing finished co-creations to wider audiences through showcasing an
 d presentation events in Ukraine and across other Creative Europe countrie
 s. Projects are expected to adapt works to new audiences through active pa
 rtner cooperation\, for example by contextualising works\, providing trans
 lation\, involving local artists\, experts and communities\, and running p
 arallel programmes. All creative and cultural sectors are eligible except 
 audiovisual. ELIGIBILITY: organisations active in the arts and culture sec
 tors\, registered in a Creative Europe country (EU and non-EU)\; Ukrainian
  partners must be registered in territory under the effective control of t
 he Ukrainian government. Proposals are submitted by a single lead applican
 t but the project must include at least two partner organisations from at 
 least two countries\, one of which is Ukraine\, with a genuine balance of 
 roles and value across partners. FUNDING: total pool €950\,000\; grants 
 up to €50\,000 covering up to 90% of project costs\, with the remaining 
 10% provided by applicants as a monetary (not in-kind) own contribution\; 
 19 to 25 grants expected. ROLLING CALL with five rounds: Round 1 deadline 
 14 September 2026\, Round 2 14 December 2026\, Round 3 15 March 2027\, Rou
 nd 4 14 June 2027\, Round 5 (final) 14 October 2027\, all 23:59 Kyiv time.
  Eligible countries (Creative Europe): Austria\, Belgium\, Bulgaria\, Croa
 tia\, Cyprus\, Czech Republic\, Denmark\, Estonia\, Finland\, France\, Ger
 many\, Greece\, Hungary\, Ireland\, Italy\, Latvia\, Lithuania\, Luxembour
 g\, Malta\, Netherlands\, Poland\, Portugal\, Romania\, Slovakia\, Sloveni
 a\, Spain\, Sweden\, Ukraine.\n\nOrganisation: IZOLYATSIA Foundation (UA)\
 , Malý Berlín (SK)\, Trans Europe Halles (SE)\nLocation: Ukraine + Creat
 ive Europe partner countries\nAward: Up to €50\,000 per project (covers 
 up to 90% of costs\; remaining 10% must be a monetary own contribution)\; 
 19 to 25 grants from a €950\,000 pot\nDuration: Per showcasing project\n
 \nMore: https://creativesunite.eu/synm/program.php?id=2695&utm_source=arti
 ficialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://creativesunite.eu/synm/program.php?id=2695&utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Ukraine + Creative Europe partner countries
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:kone-foundation-annual-grant-call-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260915
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260916
SUMMARY:Deadline: Kone Foundation: Annual Grant Call (2026)
DESCRIPTION:Kone Foundation is Finland's major private funder for academic 
 research in the humanities\, social sciences and environmental sciences\, 
 for professional artistic work across all disciplines\, and specifically f
 or multidisciplinary projects combining scholarly and artistic approaches\
 , which is where digital culture\, media arts and artistic research propos
 als land. Individuals\, working groups and legal entities with a Finnish b
 usiness ID may apply\, and artistic groups and organisations can receive u
 p to EUR 250\,000. The Finland connection is the binding constraint: a non
 -Finnish applicant needs a Finnish institutional affiliation\, Finland res
 idence\, or the work must happen in Finland\, though international collabo
 rators can join a group freely once one member is a Finnish citizen or Fin
 land-based. Psychology\, theology\, law\, business studies without an inte
 rdisciplinary element\, and medical research are not funded\, nor are mast
 er's studies\, continuing education\, building renovation\, standalone equ
 ipment purchases or hobby activity. The annual call runs 1 to 15 September
  each year\, closing 15 September 2026 at 16:00 EEST\, with decisions anno
 unced in November and December. TIMING: funding is never retroactive and p
 rojects must begin in January or later\, so a September 2026 application f
 unds work starting January 2027 at the earliest. FLAG: Kone frames its fun
 ding around artistic work and research projects rather than festival or ev
 ent hosting as such\, so an event-led application needs to be framed as an
  artistic or research project.\n\nOrganisation: Kone Foundation / Koneen S
 aatio (Finland)\nLocation: Finland. Work may be carried out abroad by Finn
 ish citizens. Projects must have a connection to Finland.\nAward: Artistic
  groups and organisations up to EUR 250\,000\; research groups typically E
 UR 200\,000 to 500\,000. Minimum project duration six months for individua
 l applicants and one month for groups\; maximum four consecutive years for
  the same project. No co-financing requirement stated. No application fee.
  No retroactive funding.\nDuration: One month to four years\; projects mus
 t start in January or later.\n\nMore: https://koneensaatio.fi/en/grants/gr
 antapplicants/criteria-for-applying/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk
 &utm_medium=referral
URL:https://koneensaatio.fi/en/grants/grantapplicants/criteria-for-applying
 /?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Finland. Work may be carried out abroad by Finnish citizens. Proje
 cts must have a connection to Finland.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:uk-irl-culture-connects-2026-27@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260731
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
SUMMARY:Deadline: British Council Ireland: UK-IRL Culture Connects Grant 20
 26/27
DESCRIPTION:The UK-IRL Culture Connects Grant 2026/27 is a British Council 
 Ireland initiative delivered in association with Arts Council Ireland\, su
 pporting the early stages of artistic collaboration between Ireland and th
 e four UK nations through in-person exchange. It prioritises creative deve
 lopment over final outputs: research and development of new ideas\, mentor
 ship\, exploring collaborative pathways with producers or partners\, exper
 imenting with new technologies or practices\, and developing initiatives t
 hat support creative exchange. WHO: applications are made by individual ar
 tists or creative practitioners working as a bilateral partnership of one 
 individual based in Ireland and one based in England\, Northern Ireland\, 
 Scotland or Wales\; applicants must be resident in Ireland or the UK for t
 he project duration\, have a proven professional track record\, be at an e
 arly or developing career stage\, and not be in full-time education. One a
 pplication per collaboration. FUNDING: up to EUR 3\,000 covering artist an
 d collaborator fees\, travel and accommodation\, studio hire\, materials\,
  and access costs. Activities must involve in-person collaboration (fully 
 remote projects are not eligible) and take place between October 2026 and 
 31 March 2027. Apply via the British Council GoodGrants platform\; an info
 rmation webinar recording and overview document are on the programme page.
  DEADLINE: 31 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: British Council Ireland / Arts C
 ouncil Ireland\nLocation: Ireland and the UK. For bilateral partnerships o
 f one individual based in Ireland and one based in England\, Northern Irel
 and\, Scotland or Wales\; in-person collaboration required.\nAward: Up to 
 EUR 3\,000 per collaboration (smaller amounts also eligible)\, covering ar
 tist fees (including your own time)\, collaborator fees\, travel and accom
 modation\, studio or space hire\, materials\, and access costs including d
 isability support. No application fee.\nDuration: Activity between October
  2026 and March 2027\; must be completed by 31 March 2027\n\nMore: https:/
 /www.britishcouncil.ie/programmes/arts/uk-irl-culture-connects-grant-20262
 7?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.britishcouncil.ie/programmes/arts/uk-irl-culture-connects-g
 rant-202627?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Ireland and the UK. For bilateral partnerships of one individual b
 ased in Ireland and one based in England\, Northern Ireland\, Scotland or 
 Wales\; in-person collaboration required.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ramdam-extended-possibilities-residency-2027@artificialnouveau.github.i
 o
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260714
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260715
SUMMARY:Deadline: RAMDAM\, un centre d'art: Extended Possibilities Residenc
 y 2027
DESCRIPTION:Extended Possibilities gives artists the opportunity to work on
  site at RAMDAM\, un centre d'art for 45 days\, a long period allowing the
 m to benefit from technical support and to present ongoing work to the pub
 lic. Artists receive on-site accommodation (a collective room for the whol
 e 45 days)\, access to a well-maintained\, up-to-date technical facility\,
  a grant to support their work\, and a lump-sum allowance for travel and v
 isas. RAMDAM is an activist space supporting artists in their artistic res
 earch\; residencies are open to artists or teams engaged in creation\, res
 earch\, or experimentation\, with no obligation to produce a finished work
 : dance\, theatre\, performance\, painting\, sculpture\, drawing\, film\, 
 video\, literary writing\, screenwriting\, digital art\, and hybrid forms 
 are all welcome. The call focuses on multidisciplinary projects and resear
 ch that break down barriers between disciplines and challenge their own fi
 eld of practice\, and considerable attention is given to how the work fits
  into a social and/or political context and resonates with our times. THE 
 CALL SUPPORTS: 1 or 2 artistic teams (RAMDAM can host at most 5 artists)\;
  performing artists of all disciplines\; projects at early stages of resea
 rch-creation and/or more advanced (residencies can be writing residencies 
 and/or stage residencies). All artists must be available for the full 45 d
 ays from 1 February to 15 March 2027 and must be from eligible countries (
 EU countries\, outermost regions\, overseas countries and territories\, an
 d some non-EU countries)\; artists from mainland (hexagonal) France cannot
  apply. The working and living spaces are wheelchair accessible\, though r
 eaching RAMDAM by public transport can be difficult for disabled people\; 
 accessibility support is available via Culture Moves Europe for residents 
 with disabilities. ALLOWANCES: EUR 1\,350 per resident for subsistence\; t
 ravel allowance EUR 400 under 5\,000 km or EUR 800 from 5\,000 km (travel 
 under 600 km must be by green means of transport unless disability or isla
 nd residence requires otherwise)\; green mobility top-up EUR 400 per resid
 ent for non-plane travel over 600 km\; visa top-up EUR 120\; outermost reg
 ions/OCT top-up EUR 175\; family top-up EUR 200 per child under 18 (housin
 g capacity is limited). TO APPLY: applications in English or French\; down
 load the residency project and administrative form documents and email the
  complete application to contact@ramdamcda.org with subject line 'extended
  possibilities - 2027' (no WeTransfer\, no important information in the em
 ail body\; reduce file sizes\; a third document may be added to help under
 stand the work). Confirmation within 7 working days\; shortlisted applican
 ts have video calls with the residency committee in mid-August. Deadline: 
 Tuesday 14 July 2026\, 11:59 p.m. NOTE: the call is arbitrarily limited to
  the first 40 applications received (still open as of 1 July 2026)\, so ap
 ply early. Made possible by the European programme Culture Moves Europe.\n
 \nOrganisation: RAMDAM\, un centre d'art\nLocation: Sainte-Foy-les-Lyon (n
 ear Lyon)\, France\; open to artists legally resident in Culture Moves Eur
 ope eligible countries (EU member states\, outermost regions\, overseas co
 untries and territories\, and some non-EU countries)\; artists from mainla
 nd (hexagonal) France cannot apply\nAward: EUR 1\,350 per resident allowan
 ce for subsistence and other costs\, plus travel allowance of EUR 400 (und
 er 5\,000 km) or EUR 800 (from 5\,000 km). Top-ups: green mobility EUR 400
  per resident (600 km or more by non-plane transport)\, visa EUR 120\, out
 ermost regions/OCT EUR 175\, family EUR 200 per child under 18. On-site ac
 commodation and technical facilities provided. Supported by Culture Moves 
 Europe.\nDuration: 45 days\, 1 February to 15 March 2027\n\nMore: https://
 ramdamcda.org/actualite-ramdam/extended-possibilities-residency-call?utm_s
 ource=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://ramdamcda.org/actualite-ramdam/extended-possibilities-residency
 -call?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Sainte-Foy-les-Lyon (near Lyon)\, France\; open to artists legally
  resident in Culture Moves Europe eligible countries (EU member states\, o
 utermost regions\, overseas countries and territories\, and some non-EU co
 untries)\; artists from mainland (hexagonal) France cannot apply
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:manuel-antonio-da-mota-prize-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: Manuel António da Mota Prize – 17th Edition (2026)
DESCRIPTION:In its 17th edition in 2026\, under the motto 'Always in Solida
 rity\,' the Manuel António da Mota Prize recognizes institutions that exc
 el in the fight against poverty and social exclusion\; the reception and i
 ntegration of migrants and refugees\; the development of rural areas and t
 erritorial cohesion\; health\; education\; employment\; family support\; i
 nnovation and social entrepreneurship\; inclusion and digital and technolo
 gical transition\; and climate transition. AWARDS: the winning application
  receives a cash prize of EUR 50\,000\; second and third place receive EUR
  25\,000 and EUR 10\,000 respectively\; the remaining seven applications (
 honourable mentions) each receive EUR 5\,000. The prize is run by the Fund
 ação Manuel António da Mota. Applications are open until 30 June 2026. 
 See the foundation's current-edition page for full rules and eligibility.\
 n\nOrganisation: Fundação Manuel António da Mota (FMAM)\nLocation: Port
 ugal. Open to private social solidarity institutions and other non-profit 
 entities working in eligible areas.\nAward: Total prize fund. The winning 
 application receives a cash prize of EUR 50\,000. Second and third place r
 eceive EUR 25\,000 and EUR 10\,000 respectively. The remaining 7 applicati
 ons (honourable mentions) each receive a cash prize of EUR 5\,000.\nDurati
 on: One-off award.\n\nMore: https://www.fmam.pt/edicao-em-curso-introducao
 /?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.fmam.pt/edicao-em-curso-introducao/?utm_source=artificialno
 uveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Portugal. Open to private social solidarity institutions and other
  non-profit entities working in eligible areas.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:stimuleringsfonds-grounding-the-cloud-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260914
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260915
SUMMARY:Deadline: Stimuleringsfonds: Open Call Grounding the Cloud 2026
DESCRIPTION:Open call from the Creative Industries Fund NL (Stimuleringsfon
 ds) for projects within digital culture that provide insight into and redu
 ce the ecological impact of digital technology. Data storage in the cloud\
 , generative AI chatbots and other everyday digital habits carry major eco
 logical consequences: the energy consumption of data centres\, the raw mat
 erials used for hardware\, and ever-growing e-waste. The Fund encourages p
 rojects that make the ecological (and therefore also social) impact of dig
 ital technologies and data consumption tangible\, question it\, and put al
 ternative working methods into practice\, around topics such as regenerati
 ve culture\, degrowth\, low-tech\, the reuse of obsolete hardware\, and re
 sponsibility for the technologies we use within digital culture. Applicati
 ons may concern new projects or the reinterpretation or further developmen
 t of existing initiatives that show scope for more depth or a changed appr
 oach. Collaborations in which designers\, makers or researchers engage wit
 h sustainability from an intersectional perspective are explicitly encoura
 ged. The grant may be used for artistic and substantive development\, rese
 arch\, collaboration\, knowledge sharing\, presentation and documentation.
  ELIGIBILITY: individual makers\, designers\, researchers or collectives w
 orking on alternative ways of handling digital technology\, registered wit
 h a Chamber of Commerce within the Kingdom of the Netherlands. Grant award
 s a maximum of EUR 30\,000\; maximum project duration one year. This call 
 is open from 17 August 2026\, 15:00 CEST until 14 September 2026\, 16:00 C
 EST. No application fee. Questions: digitalecultuur@stimuleringsfonds.nl.\
 n\nOrganisation: Stimuleringsfonds Creatieve Industrie (Creative Industrie
 s Fund NL)\nLocation: Netherlands. Requires Dutch Chamber of Commerce (KvK
 ) registration within the Kingdom of the Netherlands.\nAward: Maximum EUR 
 30\,000 per grant. No application fee.\nDuration: Project-based\; maximum 
 project duration one year.\n\nMore: https://www.stimuleringsfonds.nl/en/gr
 ants/open-call-grounding-the-cloud?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&u
 tm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.stimuleringsfonds.nl/en/grants/open-call-grounding-the-clou
 d?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Netherlands. Requires Dutch Chamber of Commerce (KvK) registration
  within the Kingdom of the Netherlands.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:stimuleringsfonds-immerse-interact-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260825
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260826
SUMMARY:Deadline: Stimuleringsfonds + Film Fund: Immerse\\Interact 2026 (se
 cond round)
DESCRIPTION:Immerse\\Interact is a joint grant scheme of the Stimuleringsfo
 nds Creatieve Industrie and the Netherlands Film Fund for immersive and in
 teractive media projects (VR\, MR\, AR and other interactive storytelling)
 . It supports artistic projects with a supporting cinematic component\, in
  which fiction or non-fiction storytelling in relation to interactive (web
 -based/mobile) or immersive technologies (XR\, room-scale projections) is 
 central. It funds both development and realisation. Development support is
  EUR 15\,000 for individual makers (plus up to EUR 5\,000 coaching\, cappe
 d at EUR 20\,000 total) or EUR 25\,000 for producers (plus up to EUR 5\,00
 0 coaching)\; the coaching contribution requires a motivation from both ap
 plicant and coach plus the coach's CV\, and the development phase must res
 ult in a usable prototype. A maximum of six development contributions are 
 awarded per round\, to keep the development and realisation budgets in bal
 ance. Realisation support is up to EUR 35\,000 for individual makers or up
  to EUR 125\,000 for producers (the Fund covers a maximum of 85 percent of
  the production budget)\; note that at realisation stage the producer may 
 not also be the director\, screenwriter or designer. A separate Presentati
 on Procedure offers presentation grants for projects previously supported 
 by Immerse\\Interact after 1 January 2022. EUR 600\,000 is available per F
 und in 2026. Open to professional makers\, collectives and producers with 
 a demonstrable track record in immersive or interactive media\; applicants
  must be registered with the Dutch Chamber of Commerce (KvK). The second 2
 026 round runs 24 June to 25 August 2026 (opens 24 June 15:00\, closes 25 
 August 16:00 CEST). No application fee. Questions: immerseinteract@stimule
 ringsfonds.nl.\n\nOrganisation: Stimuleringsfonds Creatieve Industrie and 
 the Netherlands Film Fund\nLocation: Netherlands. Requires Dutch Chamber o
 f Commerce (KvK) registration.\nAward: Development: EUR 15\,000 for indivi
 dual makers (plus up to EUR 5\,000 coaching\, max EUR 20\,000) or EUR 25\,
 000 for producers (plus up to EUR 5\,000 coaching). Realisation: up to EUR
  35\,000 for individual makers or up to EUR 125\,000 for producers (Fund c
 overs max 85 percent). No application fee.\nDuration: Project-based\, deve
 lopment and realisation phases.\n\nMore: https://www.stimuleringsfonds.nl/
 en/grants/immerse-interact-grant-scheme?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantd
 esk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.stimuleringsfonds.nl/en/grants/immerse-interact-grant-schem
 e?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Netherlands. Requires Dutch Chamber of Commerce (KvK) registration
 .
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:tba21-academy-tentacular-fellowship-ocean-space-venice-2026-2027@artifi
 cialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260705
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260706
SUMMARY:Deadline: TBA21-Academy: Tentacular Fellowship 2026-2027 (Ocean Spa
 ce\, Venice)
DESCRIPTION:TBA21-Academy\, in collaboration with NICHE Centre for Environm
 ental Humanities and the UNESCO Chair on Water\, Heritage and Sustainable 
 Development at Ca' Foscari University\, is launching the first edition of 
 the Tentacular Fellowship\, an initiative-building fellowship based at Oce
 an Space and at Ca' Foscari in Venice. Conceived as a long-term platform f
 or artistic research and ecological engagement\, Ocean Space works to deve
 lop new forms of action capable of moving beyond awareness-raising to prod
 uce real\, tangible territorial effects through situated collaboration wit
 h the communities\, practitioners\, researchers and civic actors already w
 orking within the Lagoon of Venice. The fellowship invites a practitioner 
 or collective to initiate\, consolidate or expand a situated initiative in
  the Lagoon through the creation of a Tentacular Unit: a collaborative\, i
 nterdisciplinary platform able to gather artists\, students\, researchers\
 , institutions\, local communities and other actors around a specific soci
 o-environmental challenge. Through situated research\, alliance-building a
 nd public-facing formats\, the fellow helps build the social\, institution
 al and ecological conditions for the initiative to take root and grow over
  time. STRUCTURE: the two-year fellowship runs in two phases. In Phase 1 (
 incubation) the fellow is awarded a EUR 3\,000 grant to support independen
 t research and initiative development. In Phase 2 (activation) the fellow 
 is awarded a EUR 8\,000 grant plus a EUR 15\,000 activation budget\, for t
 otal fellowship support of EUR 26\,000. Details on the application process
 \, evaluation criteria and frequently asked questions are in the full open
 -call document. Application deadline: 5 July 2026\, 11:59pm CET. Apply via
  the online form linked from the open-call page.\n\nOrganisation: TBA21-Ac
 ademy\, with NICHE Centre for Environmental Humanities and the UNESCO Chai
 r on Water\, Heritage and Sustainable Development at Ca' Foscari Universit
 y\nLocation: Ocean Space and Ca' Foscari University\, Venice\, Italy\; sit
 uated work in and with the communities of the Lagoon of Venice.\nAward: To
 tal fellowship support EUR 26\,000. Phase 1 (incubation): EUR 3\,000 grant
  for independent research and initiative development. Phase 2 (activation)
 : EUR 8\,000 grant plus a EUR 15\,000 activation budget. No application fe
 e.\nDuration: 15 months\, September 2026 to November 2027\n\nMore: https:/
 /tba21.org/oceanspace-research-tentacular-fellowship?utm_source=artificial
 nouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://tba21.org/oceanspace-research-tentacular-fellowship?utm_source=
 artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Ocean Space and Ca' Foscari University\, Venice\, Italy\; situated
  work in and with the communities of the Lagoon of Venice.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:onassis-onx-summer-school-innovation-tech-culture-2026@artificialnouvea
 u.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260621
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260622
SUMMARY:Deadline: Onassis ONX & ACE: Summer School 2026\, Innovation\, Tech
  & Culture (Worldbuilding)
DESCRIPTION:The Summer School: Innovation\, Tech & Culture\, organised by O
 nassis ONX and ACE for a third consecutive year\, invites creative profess
 ionals and teams to explore the convergence of art\, technology and sustai
 nable entrepreneurship\, bridging Culture and Digital Arts with Technology
 \, Artificial Intelligence and Entrepreneurship. The 2026 edition is again
  dedicated to 'Worldbuilding'\, a methodology that fuels innovation and fo
 sters novel entrepreneurial models: the emphasis shifts from the project o
 r end product to the narratives that frame and sustain them\, building imm
 ersive worlds around products and turning the audience into co-shapers of 
 the experience. The program challenges traditional product design and prom
 otion practices by harnessing new technologies\, art thinking and innovati
 ve design. SYLLABUS: Media & Art History\; Speculative & Interactive Desig
 n Theory\; Ethics\, Art & Technology\; Computational Creativity\; AI-enabl
 ed Tech Development\; Innovation & Entrepreneurship (business modeling and
  product validation)\; building for speed with venture capital backing\; u
 nderstanding the market and audience\; branding\, marketing and digital ch
 annels\; and IP management\, licensing and contracts. Participants attend 
 lectures and receive mentorship from keynote speakers of AUEB\, the NYU Ta
 ndon School of Engineering and Onassis ONX Fellows\, plus talks by leading
  international professionals such as artist-technologists Jiabao Li and Co
 oper Galvin. OPPORTUNITIES: access to funding opportunities and an incubat
 ion program for selected teams after completion\; development of entrepren
 eurial\, artistic and technological skills\; and networking and growth opp
 ortunities for participating companies. WHO CAN APPLY: undergraduate and p
 ostgraduate students and early-career professionals\; established professi
 onals and corporate employees in arts\, culture\, design\, marketing\, tec
 hnology and business administration. PARTICIPATION: individual application
 \, or as a member of a corporate team or company representative\; in-perso
 n attendance required\; working language English\; up to 30 participants. 
 NOTE: this is a free educational program rather than a paid grant\; no par
 ticipation or application fee. Apply via the Onassis Directory by 21 June 
 2026. Inquiries: digital@onassis.org.\n\nOrganisation: Onassis ONX\, in co
 llaboration with ACE (Athens Center for Entrepreneurship & Innovation\, AU
 EB) and NYU Tandon School of Engineering\nLocation: Athens\, Greece (Athen
 s University of Economics and Business)\; in-person attendance required.\n
 Award: Free educational program (NO participation fee and no application f
 ee)\, not a paid grant: there is no stipend\, and travel and accommodation
  are not mentioned as covered. BENEFITS: lectures and mentorship from inte
 rnationally recognised artists\, designers\, entrepreneurs and tech profes
 sionals (AUEB\, NYU Tandon\, and Onassis ONX Fellows in Athens and New Yor
 k)\; access to funding opportunities and an incubation program for selecte
 d teams after completion\; exposure to cutting-edge digital tools and inte
 rdisciplinary collaboration\; and networking. Limited to 30 participants.\
 nDuration: Two weeks\, 1 to 13 July 2026\n\nMore: https://www.onassis.org/
 open-calls-past/open-call-summer-school-2026-innovation-tech-culture?utm_s
 ource=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.onassis.org/open-calls-past/open-call-summer-school-2026-in
 novation-tech-culture?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=ref
 erral
LOCATION:Athens\, Greece (Athens University of Economics and Business)\; in
 -person attendance required.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:expobart-open-hall-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260712
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260713
SUMMARY:Deadline: Expo Bart: OPEN HALL 2026 (Free Project Space\, Technique
  & Support)
DESCRIPTION:Do you have an idea you have always wanted to carry out but can
  never find the space for? Expo Bart in Nijmegen invites you to apply for 
 OPEN HALL. From 13 November to 20 December 2026\, Expo Bart makes its proj
 ect space\, technique and helping hands available to help realise your ide
 a\, whether that is a week-long exhibition\, a one-day workshop\, a film s
 hoot\, a knitting club\, a concert series\, a film night\, a performance\,
  a dinner\, a combination of all of these\, or something completely differ
 ent. PRACTICAL: you can sign up for one or more days between 13 November a
 nd 20 December 2026\; Expo Bart is open Thursday to Sunday from 12:00 to 1
 7:00 (organising something outside opening hours can be discussed together
 )\; the 100 m2 project space is fully blackout-able\; limited technique is
  available\, namely two short-throw beamers\, a PA set (with mixer and mic
 rophones) and light spots\; and your event is of course shared via Expo Ba
 rt's channels. There is no compensation and no rent is charged. APPLY by s
 ending your idea (max 1 A4\, including photos) to info@expobart.nl with th
 e subject line 'OPEN HALL'\, stating your plan/idea\, your preferred day(s
 )\, and what you need in terms of production. Deadline: 12 July 2026.\n\nO
 rganisation: Expo Bart\nLocation: Expo Bart\, NYMA\, Waalplein 6\, Nijmege
 n\, Netherlands\nAward: No fee and no rent\, but also no artist fee or oth
 er compensation (geen vergoeding). Provides free use of a 100 m2 fully bla
 ckout-able project space\, limited technique (2 short-throw beamers\, a PA
  set with mixer and microphones\, and light spots) and helping hands\, plu
 s promotion of your event via Expo Bart's channels.\nDuration: Programme r
 uns 13 November to 20 December 2026\; book one or more days (open Thursday
  to Sunday\, 12:00-17:00\; other times negotiable)\n\nMore: https://www.ex
 pobart.nl/open-hall/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=refe
 rral
URL:https://www.expobart.nl/open-hall/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdes
 k&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Expo Bart\, NYMA\, Waalplein 6\, Nijmegen\, Netherlands
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:emergence-art-science-fellowships-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: Emergence Art+Science Fellowships: Open Call for New Comm
 issions (Emergence Festival 2027)
DESCRIPTION:Emergence at All Scales (EAAS)\, a Dutch research consortium sp
 anning mathematics\, physics\, astronomy\, chemistry and related fields (f
 unded by NWO)\, invites artists\, makers and collectives to propose new wo
 rks inspired by the theme of Emergence: how complexity arises from simple 
 ingredients\, local interactions or microscopic rules. Selected projects a
 re developed in dialogue with EAAS researchers and premiere at the first E
 mergence Festival in Amsterdam in June 2027. EAAS studies emergence across
  scales\, from quantum spacetime and the early universe to hydrodynamics\,
  quantum matter\, collective behaviour\, social segregation\, networks and
  intelligent materials\; proposals may connect to one project\, several\, 
 or the theme broadly. WELCOMED FORMS: visual art\, digital art\, film\, vi
 deo\, documentary\, installation\, exhibition\, sculpture\; performance\, 
 theatre\, dance\, music\, sound art\; and hybrid or interdisciplinary work
 s that translate research questions\, concepts\, data\, simulations\, meth
 ods or early findings into a public experience\, ideally with a life beyon
 d the festival. FELLOWS RECEIVE: up to EUR 20\,000 production budget\, dia
 logue with EAAS researchers\, support from EAAS curator Marijn Bril\, poss
 ible university office/meeting space\, festival presentation\, and possibl
 e inclusion in the EAAS digital education and art database. REQUIREMENTS: 
 a clear connection to Emergence and EAAS research that speaks to non-speci
 alist audiences\; evidence of contact with EAAS researchers during proposa
 l development\; a presentable output at the June 2027 festival\; attendanc
 e at the EAAS annual meeting in March 2027 in Nijmegen\; and a realistic t
 echnical/safety plan for festival presentation. TO APPLY by 30 June 2026: 
 a proposal up to 3 pages (concept\, research connection\, proposed researc
 hers/hosts\, audience\, work plan)\, a one-page budget\, a CV\, and a port
 folio. Shortlist interviews July-August 2026. Questions: marijn@d-iep.org.
 \n\nOrganisation: Emergence at All Scales (EAAS)\, with The Science & Cock
 tails Foundation\, Stichting Paradiso and NWA Route Kunst\nLocation: Nethe
 rlands (Amsterdam\; premiere at the Emergence Festival)\nAward: Production
  budget up to EUR 20\,000 including VAT per project (covers artist fees\, 
 materials\, equipment\, space\, travel\, accommodation\, installation and 
 presentation). Total call budget EUR 80\,000 (around four projects). No ap
 plication fee.\nDuration: Projects start September 2026\; presentable outp
 ut ready late May 2027\; premiere June 2027\n\nMore: https://www.d-iep.org
 /artsciencefellowships?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=re
 ferral
URL:https://www.d-iep.org/artsciencefellowships?utm_source=artificialnouvea
 ugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Netherlands (Amsterdam\; premiere at the Emergence Festival)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:tanztage-berlin-open-call-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260705
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260706
SUMMARY:Deadline: Tanztage Berlin Open Call 2027 (Sophiensaele)
DESCRIPTION:Tanztage Berlin\, the long-running platform at Sophiensaele for
  emerging choreographers and performance makers\, is accepting application
 s for its 2027 edition (the final edition under artistic director Mateusz 
 Szymanowka). The festival supports work across contemporary dance\, choreo
 graphy\, installation\, video and expanded performance formats\, in two tr
 acks: premieres (new productions) and revivals (completed works). ELIGIBIL
 ITY: emerging artists connected to Berlin (early in their careers\, newly 
 living in Berlin\, or without prior Berlin project funding)\; a meaningful
  professional relationship to the city is required\, though formal residen
 cy registration is not. The festival particularly welcomes projects involv
 ing marginalised perspectives\, intergenerational casts and disabled artis
 ts. Apply via the Tanztage Berlin open-call page.\n\nOrganisation: Sophien
 saele (Tanztage Berlin)\nLocation: Sophiensaele\, Berlin\, Germany\nAward:
  Premieres receive EUR 10\,000 to EUR 18\,000 production support\; revival
 s receive a EUR 5\,000 flat fee. Both tracks also receive a EUR 410 evenin
 g fee per person per performance\, rehearsal space\, technical\, curatoria
 l\, dramaturgical and PR support\, and photo/video documentation. No appli
 cation fee.\nDuration: Festival 7-23 January 2027 (rehearsals from Novembe
 r 2026)\n\nMore: https://sophiensaele.com/en?utm_source=artificialnouveaug
 rantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://sophiensaele.com/en?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_m
 edium=referral
LOCATION:Sophiensaele\, Berlin\, Germany
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:realities-in-transition-rit2-telepresence-2026@artificialnouveau.github
 .io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260629
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260630
SUMMARY:Deadline: Realities in Transition: RiT 2 Open Call #2 - Telepresenc
 e in the Digital Space
DESCRIPTION:Open call from the Realities in Transition (RiT 2 - Unwritten W
 orlds) programme for artists and designers to co-create a collective XR ar
 twork during a residency exploring telepresence and the shifting nature of
  presence in the digital age. The residency investigates how the body oper
 ates across physical and digital dimensions through motion capture and imm
 ersive environments\, treating movement as a language that can be encoded\
 , transformed and transmitted\, and opening critical and speculative persp
 ectives on authorship\, identity and corporeality. MEDIUM: motion capture 
 and immersivity. ELIGIBILITY: individual XR and immersive artists who are 
 European residents\; three artists are selected and joined by a creative t
 echnologist to work as a group. The residency alternates shared work\, cri
 tical discussion and experimentation\, from conception and prototyping to 
 a public Test Lab and audience presentation\, with a mentoring programme c
 overing XR mediation\, ethics and inclusion\, accessibility\, hybridisatio
 n of spaces\, distribution and business models. Apply via the Realities in
  Transition open-call page.\n\nOrganisation: Realities in Transition\, in 
 collaboration with MEET Digital Culture Center Milan\nLocation: Hybrid: on
 line phases plus a two-month in-person period at MEET Digital Culture Cent
 er\, Milan\, Italy\nAward: Three grants of EUR 15\,000 each (one per artis
 t)\, covering the artist's fee plus travel\, accommodation and subsistence
 \, disbursed in three installments (EUR 7\,000 on signing\, EUR 4\,000 aft
 er the Test Lab\, EUR 4\,000 at the end). Production costs of up to EUR 5\
 ,000 are covered by the host\, plus a mentoring programme. No application 
 fee.\nDuration: Six-month hybrid residency (online October-December 2026\;
  in-person at MEET Milan January-February 2027\; online February-March 202
 7)\, final project presented June 2027\n\nMore: https://www.realities-in-t
 ransition.eu/rit-2-open-call-2/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
URL:https://www.realities-in-transition.eu/rit-2-open-call-2/?utm_source=ar
 tificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Hybrid: online phases plus a two-month in-person period at MEET Di
 gital Culture Center\, Milan\, Italy
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:stimuleringsfonds-fresh-perspectives-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260825
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260826
SUMMARY:Deadline: Stimuleringsfonds: Open Call Fresh Perspectives 2026
DESCRIPTION:Open call from the Creative Industries Fund NL (Stimuleringsfon
 ds) for cross-sector collaboration projects that offer new perspectives on
  current challenges such as climate\, housing\, polarisation\, migration o
 r inequality of opportunity. The procedure runs in two phases. In Phase 1\
 , the applicant and partner use the period to prepare and kick off the pro
 ject\, further explore the theme\, intended end product and collaboration\
 , and investigate possibilities (including working on a prototype or proof
  of concept)\, concluding with a project plan\, budget and collaboration a
 greement. Phase 2\, open only to projects selected and fully completed in 
 Phase 1\, focuses on implementation and requires both a written applicatio
 n and a presentation to the advisory committee\; projects may deliver vari
 ous end products (an activity\, intervention\, event\, publication\, servi
 ce\, product or process) accompanied by a suitable form of knowledge shari
 ng such as a presentation\, symposium or publication. ELIGIBILITY: applica
 nts working with at least one partner in cross-sector collaboration\; see 
 the fund's open-call page for full eligibility details. The Phase 1 applic
 ation window runs from 19 May 2026\, 15:00 CEST to 25 August 2026\, 16:00 
 CEST.\n\nOrganisation: Stimuleringsfonds Creatieve Industrie (Creative Ind
 ustries Fund NL)\nLocation: Netherlands (Dutch fund\; cross-sector collabo
 ration)\nAward: Two-phase grant. Phase 1: ten grants of EUR 10\,000 (max 5
  months\, startup 1 December 2026 to 30 April 2027) to prepare\, explore a
 nd prototype the project. Phase 2: ten grants of EUR 50\,000 (max 12 month
 s\, implementation 1 September 2027 to 31 August 2028) for projects select
 ed and fully completed in Phase 1. No application fee.\nDuration: Phase 1 
 max 5 months\; Phase 2 (if selected) max 12 months\n\nMore: https://www.st
 imuleringsfonds.nl/en/grants/open-call-fresh-perspectives-2026?utm_source=
 artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.stimuleringsfonds.nl/en/grants/open-call-fresh-perspectives
 -2026?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Netherlands (Dutch fund\; cross-sector collaboration)
END:VEVENT
