 eau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261008
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261009
SUMMARY:Deadline: Institut francais x Cite internationale des arts Residenc
 ies 2027-2028
DESCRIPTION:Residency programme run by the Institut francais de Paris with 
 the Cite internationale des arts\, one of France's largest international a
 rtist mobility programmes\, supporting nearly seventy artists and cultural
  professionals each year. It offers furnished individual live-work studios
  in the Marais for 3\, 6 or 9 months across four quarterly windows between
  April 2027 and April 2028 (arrivals 9 April 2027\, 9 July 2027\, 8 Octobe
 r 2027\, or 7 January 2028)\, plus access to an auditorium\, exhibition sp
 aces\, rehearsal studios and shared printmaking\, screen-printing and cera
 mics workshops. The Institut francais covers the monthly cost of the studi
 o\; the artist's nominating partner organisation submits the application a
 nd must provide a stipend of at least EUR 1\,100 per month plus internatio
 nal travel\, insurance and visa fees. ELIGIBILITY: established artists and
  cultural professionals of any nationality who have lived outside France f
 or at least 5 years\, with an active professional practice\, a clearly def
 ined research or creative project\, and professional-level French and/or E
 nglish\; open across disciplines (theatre\, dance\, performance\, visual a
 rts\, music\, literature\, cinema\, architecture\, design\, digital creati
 on\, photography\, fashion\, crafts\, curating\, and more). IMPORTANT: art
 ists cannot apply directly - a partner organisation (French cultural netwo
 rk abroad\, or a French or foreign cultural organisation) must nominate an
 d support the applicant\, committing financial and professional support be
 fore\, during and after the residency. Applications open 1 July 2026\; fre
 e to apply. Deadline: 8 October 2026\, 11:59 PM CET.\n\nOrganisation: Inst
 itut francais de Paris (with Cite internationale des arts)\nLocation: Pari
 s\, France (Cite internationale des arts\, Marais\, 18 rue de l'Hotel de V
 ille\, 4th arrondissement)\nAward: Furnished\, Wi-Fi-equipped studio apart
 ment in Paris with monthly costs covered by the Institut francais. The nom
 inating partner organisation must provide a residency stipend of at least 
 EUR 1\,100 per month and cover the artist's international travel\, insuran
 ce (health\, repatriation\, liability) and any visa fees. No application f
 ee.\nDuration: 3\, 6\, or 9 months (1 to 3 consecutive quarters) between A
 pril 2027 and April 2028\n\nMore: https://www.institutfrancais.com/en/prog
 ramme/residence-and-professional-mobility/residencies-institut-francais-x-
 cite-internationale?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=refer
 ral
URL:https://www.institutfrancais.com/en/programme/residence-and-professiona
 l-mobility/residencies-institut-francais-x-cite-internationale?utm_source=
 artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Paris\, France (Cite internationale des arts\, Marais\, 18 rue de 
 l'Hotel de Ville\, 4th arrondissement)
END:VEVENT
