SUMMARY:Deadline: Vilem Flusser Residency for Artistic Research 2027
DESCRIPTION:14th iteration of the residency collaboration between transmedi
 ale and the Vilem Flusser Archive at the Universitat der Kunste Berlin (Ud
 K)\, awarded to one Berlin-based artist-researcher working in digital art 
 and moving image practices\, design\, sound and media theory. Open to arti
 sts\, researchers\, practitioners\, designers\, filmmakers and sound artis
 ts across all formats. The two-month residency comes with an artist fee of
  EUR 1\,500 per residency month\; note there are NO funds for travel or ho
 using. Duos and collectives are welcome but share the same fee. Part of tr
 ansmediale's 2027 programme (40th anniversary\, themed 'RFC 40')\, seeking
  proposals that offer alternatives to how we understand\, respond to and s
 hape our technological conditions\, moving from critique to construction. 
 Deadline: 28 August 2026\, 23:59 CEST.\n\nOrganisation: transmediale and t
 he Vilem Flusser Archive\, Universitat der Kunste Berlin (UdK)\nLocation: 
 Berlin\, Germany (open to Berlin-based artist-researchers)\nAward: Two-mon
 th residency with an artist fee of EUR 1\,500 per residency month. NO fund
 s are available for travel or housing. For duos or collectives the fee rem
 ains the same and is shared. No application fee.\nDuration: Two-month resi
 dency\n\nMore: https://transmediale.de/en/news/vilem-flusser-residency-for
 -artistic-research-2027?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=r
 eferral
URL:https://transmediale.de/en/news/vilem-flusser-residency-for-artistic-re
 search-2027?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany (open to Berlin-based artist-researchers)
