BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:movida-labs-dance-technology-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T114944Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260803
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260804
SUMMARY:Deadline: MOVIDA: Labs on Dance and Technology 2026/27
DESCRIPTION:MOVIDA is a Creative Europe co-funded consortium pairing academ
 ic institutions with dance centres across four European cities. Sixteen du
 os\, each made up of one dancer and one creative technologist\, are select
 ed across four themed labs: AI and accessibility in Bucharest\, AI and AR/
 VR in Dusseldorf\, AI and robotics in Lisbon\, and AI and mental health in
  Tallinn. Applicants are assessed on demonstrated capability in integratin
 g technology with live performance\, computational creativity\, and audien
 ce interaction. Participants selected for the labs receive fast-track cons
 ideration for the MOVIDA residencies running in 2027 and 2028.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: MOVIDA (Movement and Virtual Intelligence for the Development and Ac
 cessibility of Artists and Audiences)\nLocation: Four labs across Europe: 
 Bucharest (Romania)\, Dusseldorf (Germany)\, Lisbon and Montemor-o-Novo (P
 ortugal)\, and Tallinn (Estonia). Applications are accepted only from duos
  of one dancer and one creative technologist\; you cannot apply solo. Both
  members must reside in an EU or Creative Europe eligible country\, so Net
 herlands-based applicants qualify.\nAward: EUR 1\,200 gross per artist (EU
 R 2\,400 per duo)\, plus travel and accommodation covered\, plus a product
 ion budget of up to EUR 500 per duo. Accessibility and personal-assistance
  costs are covered by separate agreement. No application fee.\nDuration: N
 ine days per lab\, scheduled between 3 December 2026 and 11 February 2027\
 n\nMore: https://movida.dance/news/call-labs/?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://movida.dance/news/call-labs/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantd
 esk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Four labs across Europe: Bucharest (Romania)\, Dusseldorf (Germany
 )\, Lisbon and Montemor-o-Novo (Portugal)\, and Tallinn (Estonia). Applica
 tions are accepted only from duos of one dancer and one creative technolog
 ist\; you cannot apply solo. Both members must reside in an EU or Creative
  Europe eligible country\, so Netherlands-based applicants qualify.
END:VEVENT
