SUMMARY:Deadline: Association Francoise pour l'oeuvre contemporaine x Cite 
 internationale des arts: Research and Creation Residency 2027
DESCRIPTION:Launched in 2025\, this research and creation residency explore
 s the links between contemporary art\, psychiatry and the human sciences. 
 It is expressly not a therapeutic programme. It seeks artists whose practi
 ce resonates with the notion of the clinical\, meaning a situated approach
  that works closely with lived narratives and specific contexts\, and that
  engages with questions of care. The selected artist receives tailored sup
 port from Albertine de Galbert\, a clinical psychologist and exhibition cu
 rator\, including four to six working sessions\, alongside networking and 
 meeting time with programme partners. Outputs include an ongoing online jo
 urnal\, a mid-residency open studio\, and a closing presentation (exhibiti
 on\, public talk or publication) defined with the artist. Applications go 
 by email as a single PDF of no more than 15 MB to residence@francoiseartme
 mo.fr\, and require a two-page CV\, a ten-page portfolio\, a two-page stat
 ement of intent\, and a letter of recommendation from an institution or a 
 curator. A jury of four to six art and psychiatry specialists decides\, wi
 th results announced in September 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Association Franc
 oise pour l'oeuvre contemporaine / Cite internationale des arts\nLocation:
  Paris\, France (Marais site of the Cite internationale des arts). Open to
  artist-authors of any nationality and any discipline\, mid-career or esta
 blished\, with no age limit. Applicants must be comfortable working in Fre
 nch or English. Note: the studio-apartments do not meet current accessibil
 ity standards for people with disabilities.\nAward: Grant of EUR 1\,000 ne
 t of tax per month\, plus a furnished studio-apartment (20 to 35 sq m\, co
 mbining living and working space)\, international return travel to Paris a
 irports or stations\, travel insurance\, and capped research support again
 st receipts. Additional fees apply for accompanying persons. No applicatio
 n fee.\nDuration: Approximately 12 weeks\, 5 January to 26 March 2027\n\nM
 ore: https://www.citeinternationaledesarts.fr/appels-a-candidature/associa
